# Task Manager REST API (Go)

A lightweight RESTful API implemented in Go using the standard library. This project demonstrates core backend concepts including HTTP routing, JSON serialization, and basic CRUD operations.

---

## Overview

This service provides a simple in-memory task management system designed for learning and demonstration purposes. It emphasizes clarity, minimal dependencies, and idiomatic Go practices.

---

## Features

* Create, retrieve, update (mark as completed), and delete tasks
* Stateless HTTP API using `net/http`
* JSON-based request and response handling

---

## Technology Stack

* **Language:** Go (Golang)
* **Libraries:** Standard library (`net/http`, `encoding/json`)

---

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

* Go 1.18 or higher

### Installation & Run

```bash
git clone https://github.com/AbhayMishra2722/GO.git
cd GO/SimpleRestAPI
go run main.go
```

The server will start on:

```
http://localhost:8080
```

---

## API Specification

| Method | Endpoint     | Description              |
| ------ | ------------ | ------------------------ |
| GET    | /            | Service health check     |
| GET    | /tasks       | Retrieve all tasks       |
| POST   | /add         | Create a new task        |
| GET    | /done/{id}   | Mark a task as completed |
| GET    | /delete/{id} | Delete a task            |

### Example Request

**POST /add**

```json
{
  "title": "Learn Go",
  "done": false
}
```

### Example Response

```json
[
  {
    "id": 1,
    "title": "Learn Go",
    "done": true
  }
]
```

---

## Design Notes

* Data is stored in-memory and resets on server restart
* Endpoints follow simplified routing for educational purposes
* Error handling is minimal and can be extended

---

## Future Enhancements

* Persistent storage (PostgreSQL or MongoDB)
* Migration to a structured router (e.g., Gin)
* Input validation and structured error handling
* Authentication and authorization (JWT-based)
* RESTful route standardization

